rComments: I took Markets and Morals with Jordan in the Winter-2019 term. He's an excellent professor. Besides being highly knowledgeable, Jordan is an extremely pleasant individual, and a fair grader, which made me look forward to coming to class. I highly recommend taking a course with him.

Prof. Thomson definitely cares about his students but makes attendance optional so not a lot of people show up. There are no exams so after the final paper, class sizes shrink exponentially. I took two classes with him because his lectures are super interesting and I kept in touch after graduating because he's just such a great guy.
Jordan is a really nice guy and down to earth Professor. He makes complex material digestible with his organized lectures. I really enjoy his class.

Great professor! Made lectures interesting and the material was always clear. I wasn't sure if I'd enjoy the course but needed it for my program. He made it really the topics easy to grasp, would definitely take again.
